section.section:
The customer choice education section of the Commission's Web site shall include:
a clear and simple description of:
customer choice;
how customers can shop for an electricity supplier;
what kinds of competitive electricity supply options customers have, including:
the current price of standard offer service in the service territory of each electric company; and
the continuing role of the electric company in delivering electricity to a customer that chooses an electricity supplier;
fact sheets that:
answer common questions about customer choice;
advise customers about the questions customers should ask when choosing an electricity supplier; and
list the kinds of disclosures that electricity suppliers must make to customers;
a list of all electricity suppliers that have open offers to supply electricity in a customer's service area, searchable by service territory or jurisdiction; and
a statement indicating that customers who have entered into a contract with a competitive electricity supplier for electricity supply should be aware of the ending date of the contract so that they may determine, before being placed into a renewal contract with the current electricity supplier, whether they would like to:
shop for an alternative electricity supplier;
renew with the current electricity supplier; or
return to the standard offer service which may be offered at a price that is less than the renewal price offered by the current electricity supplier.
